# Allowlist: ignore everything, then include only what COPY needs.
# This way new getdeps source dirs (folly-python/, mvfst-python/, etc.)
# that appear at the repo root after local builds are excluded
# automatically — no maintenance required.
#
# If you add a new top-level dir that Dockerfile.taac needs, add a
# `!dirname/` line here. For explicit `COPY scripts/...` lines a
# missing entry produces a clear "file not found" build error; for
# the `COPY . /taac` wildcard it's silent (the file just isn't in
# the image), so audit additions accordingly.

*
# Re-include the root so BuildKit doesn't warn on `COPY . /taac`.
!.

# Selective COPYs (setup_getdeps.sh, manifests)
!scripts/
!getdeps/

# COPY . /taac (builder stage; .git/ and .projectid are excluded —
# the builder stubs them for getdeps project detection)
!CMakeLists.txt
!requirements.txt
!taac/
!thrift/
!docker/

# Top-level files that ship with the source
!README.md
!CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
!CONTRIBUTING.md
